image.altText: Katrina Gorry

items.synopsis: The Matildas are down 1-0 in their World Cup third-place playoff clash with Sweden as tempers started to flare in Brisbane. Follow all the updates in our live blog.

title.children: Matildas behind at halftime in third-place playoff with Sweden as tempers flare in Brisbane

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: There were a few enterprising moments for Australia in that opening stanza, but mostly it was played on Sweden's terms. The Matildas are honestly lucky not to be down by more as it feels like the semifinal all over again, with Australia's centre-backs battling against the speed of their opponents. This time it's Stina Blackstenius constantly charging onto long balls in behind. It earned them their penalty and goal and created so many more chances, so expect that approach to continue in the second half. Meanwhile, frustration is starting to show for Australia. There's desperation in their play and of course Katrina Gorry looks ready to square up at every opportunity. She's sitting on a yellow in this match so she has to be careful. I'm sure she doesn't want to end her tournament sent off.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HALF-TIME: The Matildas are trailing 1-0

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Fridolina Rolfo drills her left-footed strike low and to her right. Mackenzie Arnold dives the right way and sticks her left mitt out, getting within centimetres of it, but the ball finds the bottom corner. Sweden lead 1-0 after half an hour.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: SWEDEN HITS THE FRONT!!

children.content: Fridolina Rolfo drills her left-footed strike low and to her right. Mackenzie Arnold dives the right way and sticks her left mitt out, getting within centimetres of it, but the ball finds the bottom corner.
So close to another Mackenzie Arnold MOMENT.
Sweden lead 1-0 after half an hour.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Replays show Clare Hunt clearly clipped the foot of Stina Blackstenius as they ursued the ball down the right side of the box, and the referee sends Sweden to the spot. Fridolina Rolfo will take the shot. Does Mackenzie Arnold have another miracle penalty save in her?
